grep
command

ex:
grep disk_name  *.c
find file contains disk_name

full match:
ex:
ls | grep -w hello

exclusive find:
ex:
ls | grep -v test

search exact word
ls | grep -w test

search with regular expression:
grep  -v -w '[0-9]\{1,2\}'
exclude 00 ~ 99

recursive search
Read all files under each directory, recursively
use -R
ex:
grep -R hello *

